Rakuen's Covenant Council has received reports from former Conclave survey assistants in the refugee community that the Bellspine pass resonance locust swarms have reached a density that will begin interfering with any attempt to retrieve surviving Conclave geological records. The swarms are resonance-attuned and will disrupt communication, instrument function, and navigation in the pass. Six kills will reduce the swarm density below the interference threshold and allow the Council's document recovery team to enter the Lower Hollow zone safely.
Six resonance locust kills are logged and Rakuen's document recovery team has entered the Bellspine Lower Hollow zone. The Covenant Council's former Conclave survey assistants confirm that instrument readings in the zone are now stable and the swarm noise floor has dropped below the signal detection threshold. The team is proceeding toward the first documented intact Conclave survey cache in the pass, carrying the refugee community's request that any geological predictions found there be shared rather than classified.
